1
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:08,039
AN ADAPTATION OF THE NOVEL BY HUDANAJWA

2
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,600
What do you want?

3
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:14,039
Take her to the car.

4
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:16,559
- Come.
- Help. Please don't.

5
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:19,760
Help? No one's here to help you.

6
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:23,200
Get lost! Go!

7
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,240
Pick up.

8
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:33,759
Shut up if you want to live!

9
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,680
- Take whatever you want!
- I want to kill you!

10
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:40,160
- You're insane!
- Shut up!

11
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:55,200
I'm late.

12
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,440
Are you okay, miss?

13
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:57,480
Miss?

14
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,040
Your hand.

15
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:07,200
I'll take you to the clinic.

16
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,840
Where did he go?

17
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:29,280
Darling.

18
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,320
Are you okay?

19
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:34,999
Are you okay?

20
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,560
You're...

21
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,480
late.

22
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,640
Do you want anything?

23
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,480
I want to shower.

24
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,920
Darling.

25
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,040
Are you hungry?

26
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,000
I'll cook for you.

27
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:19,920
Up to you.

28
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,400
I'm sorry.

29
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,360
I apologize for being late.

30
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,640
Where did you go?

31
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,440
I had a mission.

32
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,120
A mission?

33
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,040
Where?

34
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,480
Private and confidential.

35
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,440
I understand.

36
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,200
I'm sorry.

37
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,040
On a mission?

38
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,840
A mission with Anita?

39
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:23,560
Why are you torturing me like this,
Thariq Ridzuwan?

40
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:35,560
No.

41
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,800
He wouldn't do that.

42
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,280
Ridz loves me.

43
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,440
He wouldn't do that.

44
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:53,120
<i>I will always pray
that you will never be happy!</i>

45
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:58,800
No, I can be happy with him.

46
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,360
I can.

47
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,520
<i>Ridz will marry me.</i>

48
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:11,280
<i>Then I will tell him to divorce you.</i>

49
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,600
He won't divorce me.

50
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,800
He loves me.

51
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:25,999
<i>I won't leave you in peace</i>

52
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,040
<i>until I get what's mine.</i>

53
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,400
<i>And Ridz</i>

54
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,720
<i>is mine.</i>

55
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:50,560
<i>I don't understand how someone like you
can escape unpunished.</i>

56
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:59,039
<i>You don't deserve to be happy
after taking away my wealth.</i>

57
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:01,480
<i>The thing I love most in this world!</i>

58
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:07,800
<i>You should've died!</i>

59
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,960
Darling?

60
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,240
It's been an hour.

61
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,919
Darling, the food's ready.

62
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,240
I made you something.

63
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,680
Darling.

64
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,800
Darling.

65
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:44,960
Darling.

66
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,160
What were you doing?

67
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,320
Nothing.

68
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:59,400
I'm not about to die.
If that's what you're thinking.

69
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:04,200
Darling, please don't scare me again.

70
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,200
Okay.

71
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,280
Darling.

72
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,359
Hey.

73
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,560
Hey, what's wrong?

74
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,599
Are you okay?

75
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,720
What are you looking for?

76
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,320
Looking for love.

77
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,400
Can't you see it in front of you?

78
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,280
Darling.

79
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:00,160
Darling.

80
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,240
- Good morning, sir.
- Morning.

81
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,800
Where are you coming from?

82
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,120
Commander Arman wanted to see me, sir.

83
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,239
Go on.

84
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,399
All right, sir.

85
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,320
Ma'am.

86
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,999
Was that funny?

87
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,759
A little.

88
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,040
Are they afraid of you?

89
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,879
Yeah.

90
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:28,319
I'm the head here.

91
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:32,679
Well, I have to be different at home
because I'm your husband.

92
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,840
The head?

93
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,999
You're Thariq Ridzuwan.

94
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,919
The one and only.

95
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,720
Whatever.

96
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,999
Congratulations on your wedding, Husniya.

97
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,120
Thank you, Anita.

98
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:58,040
Ridz, sorry I couldn't attend
your wedding.

99
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,800
We didn't invite you.

100
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:02,480
Baby.

101
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:07,359
You got engaged to me, but married her.

102
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,840
An interesting plot twist.

103
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,360
Anita, show some respect.

104
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:18,399
So when are we training to shoot again?

105
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,800
I'll shoot your head.

106
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,359
I'm...

107
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,559
I'm a little busy.

108
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:29,559
Kevin and Daniel can teach you.

109
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,960
I'm busy.

110
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,520
Boring.

111
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,160
I want to do it with you.

112
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:50,600
I want to learn how to shoot too!

113
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,439
What for?

114
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,760
To shoot her.

115
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,199
She's done nothing wrong.

116
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,720
Done nothing wrong?

117
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,920
What? A mission?

118
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,960
Teach Anita to shoot?

119
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:09,760
What?

120
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:13,040
Okay, hold on.

121
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,959
I sent the address and phone number.

122
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,199
I sent everything.

123
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,799
So if you're suspicious,

124
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:23,079
you can stalk her

125
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:25,039
and find out if I'm with her.

126
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,360
Okay?

127
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,280
Whatever.

128
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,719
Darling.

129
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:36,040
Can I send you to my mom's later?

130
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,720
I don't want you to stay alone. Okay?

131
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,200
Fine.

132
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,360
Look at me.

133
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,080
No.

134
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,239
Look at me, please?

135
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,880
Just look at Anita's photo!

136
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:03,240
One problem after another.

137
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,959
Hi, I'm Haider.

138
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:22,400
Husniya Radwa's bodyguard.

139
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,360
Haider will stay here until I come home.

140
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:30,840
Why doesn't he replace you?
You stay here with me.

141
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,479
- Okay?
- Darling--

142
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:35,000
- Sounds like a good plan, right? Please.
- Darling.

143
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,720
Wait for me to come home.

144
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,360
Okay?

145
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:43,600
Come.

146
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,120
I want that too. Please?

147
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:55,599
- You sure?
- Sorry.

148
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:58,959
What's up with you?
Asking Ridz to kiss your forehead?

149
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,919
Well, you don't want to kiss me.

150
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,280
Marry me first.

151
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,479
Thalia, marry me, please?

152
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,879
Yes!

153
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:08,359
Hey.

154
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,879
Stand up.

155
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:12,119
What drama are you making?

156
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:15,360
I wanted to tell you I've been
with your sister for three years.

157
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:16,919
What?

158
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:19,319
- Seriously? Three years?
- Yes.

159
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:22,480
Hold on.

160
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,639
You didn't tell me.

161
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,439
And I don't know about this.

162
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,560
Because you might not give your blessings.

163
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:31,080
Everyone knows anyway!

164
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,319
- Come here.
- Yes.

165
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,719
- Does Mom know?
- Yes.

166
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:38,800
Dad, Thaufiq, and Grandma know.
We're getting married.

167
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:42,599
Congratulations, Thalia!

168
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:45,599
- Thank you. Marriage!
- Marriage!

169
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,080
Thalia, are you serious?

170
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:49,320
You're seriously marrying him?
No one else?

171
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,000
I want to kiss my wife's forehead too.

172
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:56,080
You're asking for trouble.

173
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,840
Dear, it's okay.

174
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,240
I'm going to work now.

175
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:04,840
- Okay? Ask them if you need anything.
- Okay.

176
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:10,280
I'll take care of my future sister-in-law
with my life.

177
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:17,040
You're sweating.

178
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,720
Nervous?

179
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:26,119
I'll slap you!

180
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:27,200
Don't do that.

181
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:29,880
Take care.

182
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,519
You're getting married? Done with outfits?

183
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,959
Everything's prepared except the cake.

184
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,520
- We'll bake the cake.
- Sure.

185
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:46,559
This one's nice.
Radwa, do you want coffee?

186
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,880
I'm ordering.

187
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,320
<i>Shut up!</i>

188
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,320
Radwa?

189
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:01,560
Radwa.

190
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,639
Radwa.

191
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:06,159
Why are you moody?

192
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,279
Is it about Ridz?

193
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:09,119
If it's about him, don't worry.

194
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:11,480
He's our hero.

195
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,680
Don't worry, okay?

196
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:25,799
What was that about?

197
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,560
I don't know.

198
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:40,920
Your hand.

199
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,080
I'll take you to the clinic.

200
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:32,680
Where are you going?

201
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,560
To the shop in front.

202
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,880
I don't want to control you,
but you can't.

203
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,840
It won't take long.

204
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,080
Please?

205
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:47,800
Please.

206
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:51,200
You're cute! Want me to accompany you?

207
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:53,360
Can I go alone?

208
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:58,480
No, Radwa.
It's dangerous for you to go out alone.

209
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:03,000
I promise it'll be quick
and I'll come home immediately.

210
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,280
Please?

211
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:10,640
- Take your phone. Call if anything.
- I promise.

212
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,839
- All right.
- Cute.

213
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:15,040
- Thank you, Thalia.
- Okay.

214
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:21,520
You like seeing Ridz angry, don't you?

215
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:26,360
I'm worried too,
but we can't keep her cooped up like this.

216
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:29,439
We have to trust
she can look after herself.

217
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:32,120
I'll be in trouble
if anything happens to Radwa.

218
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:36,120
Gosh. Are you afraid of Ridz?

219
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,800
Hi.

220
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,800
Hi.

221
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:21,119
Remember me?

222
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,399
Your apron.

223
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:30,960
I've washed it.

224
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:35,680
Has your hand healed?

225
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,240
Can I treat you to a meal?

226
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:46,920
Because I helped you?

227
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,520
No need.

228
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,240
Why?

229
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:03,320
No point in helping others
if we expect something in return.

230
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,280
Okay.

231
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:16,920
Thank you.

232
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,640
Miss.

233
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:38,800
You're pretty when you smile.

234
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:41,280
But it's a pity.

235
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:43,840
You look sad.

236
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:52,040
Thank you for the apron.

237
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:06,480
Okay.

238
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:11,080
Tell me where Zahid is hiding.

239
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,600
If I don't want to,

240
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,640
what will you do?

241
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,680
Beat me up?

242
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:23,960
No, it's easy.

243
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,840
I'll take back our deal.

244
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:29,640
Just do it.

245
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:31,719
Send me to jail.

246
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,200
End of the story.

247
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,559
Jail? No.

248
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:37,000
You're not going to jail.

249
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:38,920
Instead,

250
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:41,320
I'll release you.

251
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:49,600
Why would you release me? Tell me why.

252
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:53,080
Now that is a really good question.

253
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:58,039
I want to use you as bait
for Zahid to show up.

254
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:01,360
Zahid surely wants to kill you
because you revealed his name.

255
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,120
So?

256
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:07,240
So...

257
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,640
I'll give you two options.

258
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:12,959
Do you want to die at Zahid's hands?

259
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:16,079
Or do you want to tell me
where Zahid is hiding?

260
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,120
Now I'm going to ask you one more time.

261
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,480
Where is he?

262
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,600
All right.

263
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,760
I'll follow you.

264
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:29,200
Thank you.

265
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:34,080
Release me.

266
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,440
I'll kill Zahid with my hands.

267
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:44,319
He's like me.

268
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:46,519
You hired me to be an assassin.

269
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:49,519
- What did you say, fool?
- No, it's okay.

270
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:50,960
With mad people,

271
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:54,360
ignore their shenanigans.

272
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,040
Fine.

273
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:00,080
We'll try again next time.

274
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:12,320
<i>You're pretty when you smile.</i>

275
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:14,560
But it's a pity.

276
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,400
You look sad.

277
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:22,640
How did he know?

278
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,720
"You're pretty when you smile."

279
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,640
"But it's a pity. You look sad."

280
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,679
You don't know me.

281
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:21,119
You know nothing about me.

282
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:22,400
Why did you say that?

283
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,959
Because I know someone

284
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:28,960
with the same smile.

285
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,920
Who?

286
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,280
Tell me your story.

287
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:37,360
I'll tell you mine.

288
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:12,200
You're here too?

289
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,879
It's stifling. Get lost.

290
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:17,280
And the café is hot today.

291
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,359
No.

292
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,359
Can you go to another place?

293
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:25,319
This is my favorite café!

294
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:26,760
Is this your dad's café?

295
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:29,759
- No.
- Then?

296
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,919
You should leave.

297
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,359
You should get lost!

298
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:33,639
What's your problem?

299
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,000
Don't push me!

300
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:45,880
Leave.

301
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:49,559
Hey, do you think this is your dad's café?

302
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:51,400
How dare you tell us to leave?

303
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:54,280
This isn't my dad's café.

304
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:56,840
It's mine.

305
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:59,160
Should I call the police?

306
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,559
Honey, come on. We'll go to another café.

307
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:04,480
Let him go!

308
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:12,080
Must I always rescue you?

309
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,840
I didn't ask you to.

310
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,560
My mom.

311
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:24,920
It's my mom.

312
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,520
She smiles beautifully.

313
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:30,160
But it's a pity.

314
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,600
She seems sad.

315
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,360
Radwa.

316
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,440
What's this?

317
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:39,520
Radwa.

318
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:42,679
My goodness!

319
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:45,960
Oh my God! Who did this?

320
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:49,880
Ridz! Where's Ridz?

321
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:53,719
Thalia, call Thaufiq. Now.

322
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,640
Haider, call Ridz now.

323
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:04,440
Thariq, you have to come home now.

324
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,840
We found something.

325
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,120
Open it.

326
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:44,560
He was here. Damn it.

327
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,320
Ridz.

328
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:52,920
- Calm down.
- What do you mean, "calm down"?

329
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:55,520
He almost kidnapped Radwa!

330
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:59,240
And he came to my house
and harassed Radwa!

331
00:27:01,080 --> 00:27:02,639
He will die.

332
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:04,599
I know you're stressed out.

333
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:06,639
But Radwa is scared too.

334
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:08,720
I think you should keep her company.

335
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:12,960
I will find him.

336
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:16,480
I'll kill him. Just watch.

337
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,760
Thaufiq, how's Radwa doing?

338
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,160
She's okay.

339
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:36,680
But she's still in a state of shock.

340
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:40,400
Don't leave her alone tonight, okay?

341
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:45,960
Mom. Thalia.

342
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,040
Thanks for taking care of Radwa.

343
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:53,600
Darling, are you okay?

344
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,359
Hey. Shush.

345
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:00,679
Come here. I'm right here.

346
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:02,519
I'm with you.

347
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:04,640
I won't leave you, okay?

348
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:07,200
Dear.

349
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:09,599
He's back.

350
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:10,960
No, darling.

351
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,719
It's true. He's here again.

352
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:15,079
No, darling!

353
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:17,640
- How do you know?
- Because he's dead!

354
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:28,440
I killed him. I'm sorry, okay?
I didn't mean to get angry.

355
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,720
If you killed him,

356
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:42,760
who came just now?

357
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,919
I'm asking you!

358
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:42,400
Where is Zahid hiding?

359
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:48,440
I told you I don't know.

360
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:51,439
You blasted fool!

361
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:52,439
Ridz.

362
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,920
Calm down.

363
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,360
If he dies, we get nothing.

364
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,440
No matter what happens,

365
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:09,960
Zahid will die.

366
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,440
Now, I'm asking you this.

367
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:17,400
Do you want him to die alone
or do you want to join him? Answer me.

368
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:21,960
You don't get it, huh?

369
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:26,640
Fool!

370
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,600
- Arrest him alive.
- No promises.

371
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:41,560
- We need him alive, Thariq.
- After what he did to Radwa?

372
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:45,360
Don't kill Zahid.

373
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:50,320
We don't know
if he's still hiding the kids somewhere.

374
00:31:52,520 --> 00:31:56,320
And we have to investigate
where he took them.

375
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:59,639
Basically, we arrest him,

376
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:01,159
get information,

377
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:03,320
and then you can do whatever you want.

378
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:10,800
This is an order.

379
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,000
Hey!

380
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:37,160
This...

381
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:41,560
is for what you did to my wife, bastard.

382
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,000
What are you doing?

383
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,400
We have orders, Thariq.

384
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:21,720
Don't disobey.

385
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:43,400
Alive, Thariq!

386
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,760
I wanted him to die
for what he did to Radwa.

387
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,200
But I killed him

388
00:37:33,560 --> 00:37:35,040
to save you.

389
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,440
My coffee isn't good enough
for you to wait in line for.

390
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,880
You're here early.

391
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:26,120
Ridz is a perfect husband.

392
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:29,520
He always makes me happy.

393
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:33,480
He makes me feel safe
whenever I'm with him.

394
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:37,160
He always makes you happy?

395
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:40,000
He makes you feel safe
whenever you're with him?

396
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,440
But?

397
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:48,680
But he's not always around.

398
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:51,880
Where does he go?

399
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,040
To work.

400
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,200
I'm not being selfish.

401
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,799
I understand that's his responsibility.

402
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:01,719
Not only for me,

403
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:04,400
but also for the country.

404
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,520
What's his job?

405
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,720
He's in the special forces.

406
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:20,600
No wonder you smile like my mom.

407
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:24,840
You smile, but you look sad.

408
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:33,320
I hate people in uniform.

409
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,480
My dad was a soldier.

410
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:44,920
A soldier who's willing to sacrifice
for the country.

411
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:49,400
But he's a failure as a father.

412
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:55,240
And a husband who's very good
at neglecting his wife.

413
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:12,520
<i>A soldier who's willing to sacrifice
for the country.</i>

414
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,400
<i>But he's a failure as a father.</i>

415
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:20,960
<i>And a husband who's very good
at neglecting his wife.</i>

416
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:58,040
Darling.

417
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,960
Why are you carrying a bag?

418
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:05,440
For fun.

419
00:41:06,040 --> 00:41:09,280
I want to take you away
from this mad world.

420
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:11,560
Where to?

421
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:13,240
To my hometown.

422
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:16,600
For Haider and Thalia's solemnization.

423
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:19,519
After that, we'll go on a holiday.

424
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:21,040
Another honeymoon.

425
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:22,560
Okay?

426
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:24,320
Are you on leave?

427
00:41:25,160 --> 00:41:29,720
Yes. I'm on a long leave for you.

428
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:35,920
I miss you, dear.

429
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:42,000
Darling.

430
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:46,040
I promise you

431
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:51,480
no one will harm us again.

432
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:57,559
I'll always make you smile

433
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:59,840
and be sure you're happy with me.

434
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:03,040
I promise.

435
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:37,400
Come on.

436
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:50,279
- Come on.
- Is the water boiling?

437
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,079
- Yes.
- All right.

438
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:54,639
- And you're taking your time.
- Peace be upon you.

439
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:57,759
- And upon you too.
- What are you cooking? It smells so good.

440
00:42:57,760 --> 00:42:59,519
Radwa!

441
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:01,959
- I missed you.
- Mom.

442
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:03,280
Turn down the heat.

443
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:13,519
If I can't get Ridz,

444
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,600
neither can you.

445
00:43:16,560 --> 00:43:17,640
- What's this?
- What?

446
00:43:18,240 --> 00:43:19,919
- My gosh!
- What have you done?

447
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:22,439
- My goodness, my grandchild.
- My gosh, Aina!

448
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:23,520
Mom.

449
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,280
Have you lost your mind?

450
00:43:30,120 --> 00:43:32,960
<i>It's only been six months
since we got married.</i>

451
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:36,120
<i>Having a child is the last thing
on my mind.</i>

452
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:38,520
It's all God's providence.

453
00:43:39,200 --> 00:43:41,079
I've thought it through.

454
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:43,159
I agree to have a small wedding ceremony.

455
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:45,000
Solemnization is the most important thing.

456
00:43:45,640 --> 00:43:48,200
You don't deserve Ridz.

457
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:50,719
You're barren!

458
00:43:50,720 --> 00:43:53,559
If I really can't get pregnant,

459
00:43:53,560 --> 00:43:55,999
- you have to leave me--
- Shush.

460
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:57,640
What are you saying?

461
00:43:58,880 --> 00:43:59,920
Crazy!

462
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:03,679
You're insane!

463
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:04,960
NEXT EPISODE PREVIEW
